      <tbody>
        <tr> <th scope="row"></th>
          <td><strong>Stagehand</strong></td>
          <td>Provide manual labor for the set up and tear down
            of an event as instructed by the crew chief.</td>
        </tr>
        <tr> <th scope="row"></th>
          <td><strong>Truck Loader</strong></td>
          <td>Unload and load crates and equipment from trucks.</td>
        </tr>
        <tr> <th scope="row"></th>
          <td><strong>Electrician</strong></td>
          <td>Perform the electrical connections as required.</td>
        </tr>
          <tr> <th scope="row"></th>
          <td><strong>Carpenter</strong></td>
          <td>Build or set up staging, scenery, and backdrops.
          Must have experience with carpentry tools and techniques.</td>
        </tr>
          <tr> <th scope="row"></th>
          <td><strong>Ground Rigger</strong></td>
          <td>Provide necessary support for the up riggers. Must know basic knots,
          other rigging requirements, and how to correctly pack rigging crates.</td>
        </tr>
          <tr> <th scope="row"></th>
          <td><strong>Up Rigger</strong></td>
          <td>Set rigging points and manipulate rigging lines, hoists,
          and pulling gear to lift the theatrical sound, lighting, and sets.
          Must be trained in rigging practices and procedures. </td>
        </tr>
          <tr> <th scope="row"></th>
          <td><strong>Forklift Driver</strong></td>
          <td>Operate forklifts to load and unload materials and equipment.
          All forklift drivers must be certified.</td>
        </tr>
